      "title": "Number Spiral",
      "topics": [],
      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": true,
      "shortest": false,
      "solution": "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n    int n;\n    cin >> n;\n\n    vector<vector<int>> grid(n, vector<int>(n, 0));\n    \n    int x = 0, y = 0;\n    int num = 1;\n    int current_size = n;\n    \n    while (current_size > 0) {\n        for (int entry = 0; entry < current_size; entry++) {\n            grid[x][y] = num++;\n            if (entry < current_size - 1) {\n                y++;\n            }\n        }\n\n        for (int entry = 0; entry < current_size - 1; entry++) {\n            x++;\n            grid[x][y] = num++;\n        }\n\n        for (int entry = 0; entry < current_size - 1; entry++) {\n            y--;\n            grid[x][y] = num++;\n        }\n\n        for (int entry = 0; entry < current_size - 2; entry++) {\n            x--;\n            grid[x][y] = num++;\n        }\n\n        y++;\n        current_size -= 2;\n    }\n\n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {\n            cout << grid[i][j];\n            if (j < n - 1) cout << \" \";\n        }\n        cout << endl;\n    }\n    return 0;\n}",
      "statement": "Write a program that displays the number spiral pattern for a given size. The pattern should consist of consecutive numbers, starting with 1 in the top-left corner. Output each row of the pattern as a series of numbers (see example below).",
