    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Write a program that displays the number spiral pattern for a given size. The pattern should consist of consecutive numbers, starting with 1 in the top-left corner. Output each row of the pattern as a series of numbers (see example below).</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\">A single positive integer, representing the size of the spiral grid.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">n lines, each containing n numbers separated by single spaces, forming the spiral pattern.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">The size will be between 4 and 10, inclusive.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">4</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">1 2 3 4\n12 13 14 5\n11 16 15 6\n10 9 8 7</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
